ValueDomain.preferredName: Acute Leukemia of Ambiguous Lineage And Other Myeloid Neoplasm Type
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: An acute leukemia in which the blasts lack sufficient evidence to classify as myeloid or lymphoid or they have morphologic and/or immunophenotypic characteristics of both myeloid and lymphoid cells. (WHO, 2001)_An article which expresses the relation of connection or addition. It is used to conjoin a word with a word, a clause with a clause, or a sentence with a sentence._Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned._A clonal (malignant) proliferation of myeloid cells originating from a primitive stem cell._Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A clinically aggressive neoplasm derived from the precursors of plasmacytoid dendritic cells (also called professional type I interferon-producing cells or plasmacytoid monocytes), with a high frequency of cutaneous and bone marrow involvement and leukemic dissemination. (WHO 2017)

Concepts.definition: A clinically aggressive neoplasm derived from the precursors of plasmacytoid dendritic cells (also called professional type I interferon-producing cells or plasmacytoid monocytes), with a high frequency of cutaneous and bone marrow involvement and leukemic dissemination. (WHO 2017)

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage in which the blasts do not express markers specific to myeloid or lymphoid lineage.

Concepts.definition: A rare acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage in which the blasts do not express markers specific to myeloid or lymphoid lineage.

PermissibleValues.value: Mixed phenotype acute leukemia (MPAL) with BCR::ABL1 fusion

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia with BCR-ABL1 Fusion
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts carry the chromosomal translocation t(9;22)(q34.1;q11.2) that results in BCR-ABL1 gene fusion. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

Concepts.longName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia with BCR-ABL1 Fusion
Concepts.definition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts carry the chromosomal translocation t(9;22)(q34.1;q11.2) that results in BCR-ABL1 gene fusion. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

PermissibleValues.value: Mixed phenotype acute leukemia with KMT2A rearrangement

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia with KMT2A Rearrangement
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts carry a translocation between the KMT2A gene at 11q23.3 and another gene partner. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

Concepts.longName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia with KMT2A Rearrangement
Concepts.definition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts carry a translocation between the KMT2A gene at 11q23.3 and another gene partner. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

PermissibleValues.value: Mixed-phenotype acute leukemia with ZNF384 rearrangement

ValueMeaning.preferredName: B Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia with ZNF384 Rearrangement
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: B-acute lymphoblastic leukemia associated with ZNF384 gene rearrangement. The prognosis is variable.

Concepts.longName: B Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia with ZNF384 Rearrangement
Concepts.definition: B-acute lymphoblastic leukemia associated with ZNF384 gene rearrangement. The prognosis is variable.

PermissibleValues.value: Acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage with BCL11B rearrangement

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Acute Leukemia of Ambiguous Lineage with BCL11B Rearrangement
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage characterized by the presence of BCL11B gene rearrangement.

Concepts.longName: Acute Leukemia of Ambiguous Lineage with BCL11B Rearrangement
Concepts.definition: A rare acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage characterized by the presence of BCL11B gene rearrangement.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express B-lymphoid and myeloid lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

Concepts.definition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express B-lymphoid and myeloid lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express T-lymphoid and myeloid lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

Concepts.definition: A rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express T-lymphoid and myeloid lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

ValueMeaning.administrativeNotes: 2023.9.5 Alt VM added per ticket request CADSR0002816. ak

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia, Rare Types
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A very rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express combinations of B, T, myeloid, and megakaryocytic lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

Concepts.longName: Mixed Phenotype Acute Leukemia, Rare Types
Concepts.definition: A very rare mixed phenotype acute leukemia in which the blasts express combinations of B, T, myeloid, and megakaryocytic lineage markers but are negative for KMT2A rearrangement and t(9;22)(q34;q11.2) translocation. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.

ValueMeaning.administrativeNotes: 2023.9.5 Alt VM added per ticket request CADSR0002816. ak

PermissibleValues.value: Acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage, not otherwise specified

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Acute Leukemia of Ambiguous Lineage, Not Otherwise Specified
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage, expressing combinations of markers that do not allow for its classification as either acute undifferentiated leukemia or mixed phenotype acute leukemia, and definitive classification along a single lineage is difficult. (WHO 2017)

Concepts.longName: Acute Leukemia of Ambiguous Lineage, Not Otherwise Specified
Concepts.definition: Acute leukemia of ambiguous lineage, expressing combinations of markers that do not allow for its classification as either acute undifferentiated leukemia or mixed phenotype acute leukemia, and definitive classification along a single lineage is difficult. (WHO 2017)
